**Title:** CON - AppSec Challenge - SAINTCON

**Description:** This challenge invites participants to find and fix vulnerabilities in source code. Competitors will clone a repository, identify vulnerabilities, address issues, and submit their code to earn scores based on the difficulty of the vulnerabilities they fix.

**Key Information:**
- **Organizers:** @Sketrik & @l4wke
- **Challenge Focus:** Competing to fix web application vulnerabilities using varying programming languages in a microservices architecture.
- **Requirements:** Basic programming knowledge recommended; help available through the AppSec community.
- **Contest Duration:** 
  - Starts: Tuesday at 12 PM
  - Ends: Friday at 9 AM
- **Booth Hours:**
  - Tuesday: 10:30 AM – 5:00 PM
  - Wednesday: 10:30 AM – 5:00 PM
  - Thursday: 9:00 AM – 5:00 PM
  - Friday: 9:00 AM – 10:00 AM
- **Rules:**
  - Hacking the challenge site is forbidden.
  - Submissions should be limited to specific files; max file size is 4MB.
  - Only one submission allowed every 5 minutes.
  - Prizes awarded for top scores.

**Website for Details:** [AppSec Community](https://appsec.saintcon.community/)

**Media:**
- Main Image: AppSec Challenge Splash 2024
- Desktop wallpaper available for download.

**SEO Information:**
- **Canonical:** https://saintcon.org/con-appsec-challenge/
- **Open Graph URL:** https://saintcon.org/con-appsec-challenge/
- **Twitter Card:** Summary with an image.

This challenge is presented by SAINTCON, which is committed to fostering a vibrant community of cybersecurity enthusiasts.